Emil Protalinski, writing for The Next Web:
 Facebook today introduced 15-second video ads, which will start playing without sound as they appear on screen and stop if you scroll past. If you tap the video, it will expand into a full-screen view with sound. The company says users can expect to start seeing these new ads &ldquo;over the next few months.&rdquo;
 Facebook is not the first to bring auto-play videos to mobile devices — both Instagram and Vine did the same last year.

